(\cos{x})^2+(\sin{x})^2=1
(\sin {x}\times \sin {x}\times \cos {x})^2+(\cos {x}\times \cos {x}\times \sin {x})^2=(\sin {x}\times \cos {x})^2
\frac{(\sin {x}\times \sin {x}\times \cos {x})^2}{(\sin {x}\times \cos {x})^2}=(\sin{x})^2
\frac{(\cos {x}\times \cos {x}\times \sin {x})^2}{(\sin {x}\times \cos {x})^2}=(\cos{x})^2
(\text{Hypotenuse,side,side})=(x\sqrt{2},x,x)
